> Our Crispy Potato Topped Harissa Bean Bowl is a delicious veggie option that makes it easy to eat more veg in your diet and try something new!

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @Roasted Spice and Herb Blend{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @Mixed Beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Add the mixed beans, @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Red Wine Stock Paste{28%g} and @water{100%ml} to a large #saucepan{}.

Put on medium-high heat, bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain the @sweetcorn{160%g} in a sieve.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir the sweetcorn into the pan.

Add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir the @Harissa Paste{50%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @Honey{1%tbsp} and @Butter{20%g} into the pan until combined.

Season with salt and pepper. Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

When everything's ready, share the harissa beans between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the roasted potatoes and drizzle with the @Soured Cream{75%g}.

Top with the @Wild Rocket{20%g} and drizzle with some @olive oil{} to finish. Enjoy!